{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01M9KcBxg1oyLksZHNumMWcE","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Mixed Berry Jam.generated.22.txt"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"10f3291a-c249-48df-81bc-02c14533ee15","uuid":"464a76b3-a480-4fab-b981-50f56e5faf89","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Mixed Berry Jam.generated.22.txt","content":"MIXED\nBERRY\nJAM\n\nMakes approximately 800ml (enough for 3-4 jars)\nPreparation time: 20 minutes | Cooking time: 45 minutes\n\nINGREDIENTS:\n400g blackberries\n300g raspberries\n250g blueberries\n650g sugar (or jam sugar with pectin)\nJuice of 1 lemon\n1 vanilla pod, split (optional)\nPinch of sea salt\n\nEQUIPMENT:\nSterilized jam jars\nMuslin cloth\nWooden spoon\nSugar thermometer (helpful but not essential)\n\nMETHOD:\n1. Combine berries, sugar, and lemon juice in a large, heavy-bottomed pot.\n2. Heat gently, stirring occasionally, until sugar dissolves completely.\n3. Bring to a rolling boil. Add vanilla pod seeds if using.\n4. Maintain boil for 30-40 minutes, stirring frequently. Skim foam as it rises.\n5. Test for setting point: place small spoonful on a cold plate. Push with finger—\nif it wrinkles, jam is ready. Temperature should reach 104°C.\n6. Remove from heat. Let cool 5 minutes before pouring into sterilized jars.\n7. Seal immediately. Label with date and berry varieties.\n\nSTORAGE: Keeps for up to 18 months in cool, dark place. Refrigerate after opening.\n\nNOTES: Do not skip lemon juice—it provides acid and helps jam set. For chunky texture,\nadd berries in stages. For smooth jam, pass through sieve after cooking.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
